            <div class="opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper ">

                    <span class="opener__topics ">
            <a class="opener__topics-link " href="https://www.propublica.org/topics/education">Education</a>
        </span>
    
    <h1 class="opener__hed  opener__hed--small" >        Private Schools, Public Money: School Leaders Are Pushing Parents to Exploit Voucher Programs
    </h1>

    <h2 class="opener__dek " >        Voucher expansions have unleashed a flood of additional taxpayer dollars to the benefit of families already enrolled in private schools. In Ohio, some schools are now “strongly encouraging” parents to apply for vouchers, regardless of need or income.
    </h2>

    </div> <!-- Close .opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper -->

</div>
        <div class="article-meta-2
    " data-pp-location="article meta">

    
    <hr class="article-meta-2__rule article-meta-2__rule--wide"/>

    <div class="article-meta-2__section-byline">
        <span class="article-meta-2__byline" data-pp-location="article byline">
            by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/alec-macgillis">Alec MacGillis</a>        </span>

        
